text: The James Coleman House was built in Swainsboro, Georgia during 1900–1904. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1992. In 2017, it was a bed and breakfast inn, the Coleman House Inn. It is a two-story wood- frame Queen Anne-style house with Classical Revival-style details. It has 11 fireplaces. On the south side of the property is a contributing one-story, brick hot house, used as a tool shed. There is also a non-contributing four- car garage.
